i International Airport|Dubai\u2013International]], [[Kazi Nazrul Islam Airport|Durgapur]], [[Frankfurt Airport|Frankfurt]], [[Gaya Airport|Gaya]], [[Dabolim Airport|Goa]], [[Lokpriya Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport|Guwahati]], [[Hong Kong International Airport|Hong Kong]], [[Rajiv Gandhi International Airport|Hyderabad]], [[Imphal Airport|Imphal]], [[Devi Ahilya Bai Holkar Airport|Indore]], [[Jaipur International Airport|Jaipur]], [[Jammu Airport|Jammu]], [[King Abdulaziz International Airport|Jeddah]], [[Jodhpur Airport|Jodhpur]], [[Hamid Karzai International Airport|Kabul]], [[Kannur International Airport|Kannur]], [[Tribhuvan International Airport|Kathmandu]], [[Khajuraho Airport|Khajuraho]], [[Cochin International Airport|Kochi]], [[Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport|Kolkata]], [[Calicut International Airport|Kozhikode]], [[Kushok Bakula Rimpochee Airport|Leh]], [[Heathrow Airport|London\u2013Heathrow]], [[Chaudhary Charan Singh Airport|Lucknow]], [[Adolfo Su\u00e1rez Madrid\u2013Barajas Airport|Madrid]], [[Velana International Airport|Mal\u00e9]], [[Melbourne Airport|Melbourne]], [[Milan Malpensa Airport|Milan\u2013Malpensa]], [[Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj International Airport|Mumbai]], [[Muscat International Airport|Muscat]], [[Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar International Airport|Nagpur]], [[Al Najaf International Airport|Najaf]], [[Shri Guru Gobind Singh Ji Airport|Nanded]], [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|New York\u2013JFK]], [[Newark Liberty International Airport|Newark]],<!--DON'T REMOVE. AI191 (DEL-BOM-EWR) / AI144 (EWR-BOM-DEL) is a one stop direct flight which completes its journey in same aircraft making a layover at BOM.--> [[Charles de Gaulle Airport|Paris\u2013Charles de Gaulle]], [[Jay Prakash Narayan Airport|Patna]], [[Veer Savarkar International Airport|Port Blair]], [[Pune Airport|Pune]], [[Swami Vivekananda Airport|Raipur]], [[Rajkot Airport|Rajkot]], [[Birsa Munda Airport|Ranchi]], [[King Khalid International Airport|Riyadh]], [[Leonardo da Vinci\u2013Fiumicino Airport|Rome\u2013Fiumicino]], [[San Francisco International Airport|San Francisco]], [[Incheon International Airport|Seoul\u2013Incheon]]<!--DON'T REMOVE. AI310 (BOM-DEL-HKG-ICN) / AI317 (ICN-HKG-DEL-BOM) is a direct (stopping) flight which completes its journey in same aircraft making layovers at DEL and HKG.-->, [[Shanghai Pudong International Airport|Shanghai\u2013Pudong]],  [[Singapore Changi Airport|Singapore]], [[Sheikh ul-Alam International Airport|Srinagar]], [[Stockholm Arlanda Airport|Stockholm\u2013Arlanda]], [[Surat Airport|Surat]], [[Sydney Airport|Sydney]], [[Ben Gurion Airport|Tel Aviv]], [[Trivandrum International Airport|Thiruvananthapuram]], [[Tirupati Airport|Tirupati]], [[Narita International Airport|Tokyo\u2013Narita]], [[Toronto Pearson International Airport|Toronto\u2013Pearson]], [[Maharana Pratap Airport|Udaipur]], [[Vadodara Airport|Vadodara]], [[Lal Bahadur Shastri Airport|Varanasi]], [[Vienna International Airport|Vienna]], [[Vijayawada Airport|Vijayawada]], [[Visakhapatnam Airport|Visakhapatnam]], [[Washington Dulles International Airport|Washington\u2013Dulles]],<!--DON'T REMOVE. AI103 (DEL-BOM-IAD) / AI104 (IAD-BOM-DEL) is a one stop direct flight which completes its journey in same aircraft making a layover at BOM.--> [[Yangon International Airport|Yangon]]|<ref name=\"AI\">{{cite web|url=https://book.airindia.in/itd/itd/lang/en/travel/schedules|title=Air India and Alliance Air schedule list|accessdate=8 November 2018|publisher=airindia.in}}</ref>\n<!--  -->\n| [[Air India Express]] | [[Abu Dhabi International Airport|Abu Dhabi]], [[Coimbatore International Airport|Coimbatore]], [[Dubai International Airport|Dubai\u2013International]], [[Madurai Airport|Madurai]], [[Tiruchirappalli International Airport|Tiruchirappalli]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/289883/air-india-express-expands-tiruchirapalli-network-in-s20/|title=Air India Express expands Tiruchirapalli network in Nv S20|work=Airlineroute|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref> |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.airindiaexpress.in/en/about-us/express-route-map-schedule|title=Express Route Map and Schedule|publisher=Air India Express|accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref>\n<!--  -->\n| [[Air Mauritius]] | [[Sir Seewoosagur Ramgoolam International Airport|Mauritius]] |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.airmauritius.com/Timetable/TimeTable.pdf|title=Flight Timetable|publisher=Air Mauritius|accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref>\n<!--  -->\n| {{nowrap|[[AirAsia India]]}} |[[Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel International Airport|Ahmedabad]], [[Bagdogra Airport|Bagdogra]], [[Kempegowda International Airport|Bangalore]], [[Chandigarh Airport|Chandigarh]], [[Chennai International Airport|Chennai]], [[Dabolim Airport|Goa]], [[Lokpriya Gopinath Bordoloi International Airport|Guwahati]], [[Rajiv Gandhi International Airport|Hyderabad]], [[Imphal Airport|Imphal]], [[Devi Ahilya Bai Holkar Airport|Indore]], [[Jaipur International Airport|Jaipur]], [[Cochin International Airport|Kochi]], [[Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport|Kolkata]], [[Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj International Airport|Mumbai]], [[Pune Airport|Pune]], [[Birsa Munda Airport|Ranchi]], [[Sheikh ul-Alam International Airport|Srinagar]] |<ref name=\"AirAsia\">{{cite web|url=https://www.airasia.com/my/en/where-we-fly/flight-schedule.page|title=AirAsia flight schedule|publisher=airasia.com|accessdate=8 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004023913/https://www.airasia.com/my/en/where-we-fly/flight-schedule.page|archive-date=4 October 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n<!--  -->\n| [[AirAsia X]] | [[Kuala Lumpur International Airport|Kuala Lumpur\u2013International]] |<ref name=\"AirAsia\"/>\n<!--  -->\n| [[Alitalia]] | [[Leonardo da Vinci\u2013Fiumicino Airport|Rome\u2013Fiumicino]] |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alitalia.com/en_gb/fly-alitalia/news-and-activities/news/flight-schedule-info.html|title=